<head>COMPASS</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">羅盤</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>TOOL USED to DEFINE the DIRECTIONS WITH.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. Sīnán 司南 is the predecessor of a compass; it was made of a natural magnetic iron.</p>
<p>2. Zhǐnánzhēn 指南針 is a compass pointing in the north-southern direction, which was made of a magnetic iron.</p>
<p>3. Zhǐnánchē 指南車 refers to a chariot pointing to the world directions; it came to be used by the emperors after the Jin dynasty.</p>
        </div>
